</p><p>If we are to make nuclear power contribute a major portion of our energy supply, we <b>must</b> start reprocessing fuel (with the concomitant problems). Among other things, without reprocessing fuel (to recover and use the un-burned uranium), we run out of uranium.
</p><p>With that said: it is a solvable problem.</p></div>
