	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64679132"><p>The problem with initiatives likes these is they start out with good intentions but always lead to two outcomes: unintentional disastrous results or suppression of research that highlights the potential for disastrous results but the project moves on regardless. Lead in gasoline, DDT, the plastics industry and their BS recycling claims, oil company suppression of global warming research<nobr> <wbr></nobr>... the list goes on. Finding alternatives to fossil fuels is the only way forward. Quick fixes do not exist.</p></div>
	</div>

