<div id="comment_status_64679134" class="commentstatus"></div>
<div id="comment_64679134" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64679134" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a rel="nofollow" id="comment_link_64679134" name="comment_link_64679134" href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23410378&amp;cid=64679134" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64679134)" >They missed one of the major downsides.</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64679134" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64679134); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>5</a>, Insightful)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~tragedy">tragedy</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~tragedy">( 27079 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64679134">		
		on Sunday August 04, 2024 @12:57AM (<span class="ind"></span><a rel="nofollow" href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23410378&amp;cid=64679134">#64679134</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64679134"><p>One of the major dowsides not mentioned in the summary is due to how this cools the planet. The greenhouse effect works through sunlight coming down to the surface and producing heat, which tries to leave the planet as IR, but greenhouse gases effectively trap the IR, leading to heating. This technique does not counter the greenhouse effect. It leaves the greenhouse effect just as strong, but it lets less sunlight in. This is a bad thing, because we use sunlight and are, in fact, dependent on it. If anything like this is implemented globally, how are we going to deal with the inevitable loss of sunlight for growing crops, solar power, etc.? A dimmer world means less food. Will farmers be compensated? Will more farmland be opened up to compensate for the loss?</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64679134">
<span class="ind"></span><a id="reply_link_64679134" class="btn link" href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23410378&amp;op=Reply&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;pid=64679134" onclick="D2.replyTo(64679134); return false;">Reply to This</a> 	<a rel="nofollow" href="#" class="comment_share_toggle btn link">Share</a>
